OL,3,CWoman, 95, left lying on pavement for
OL,4,Cover five hours before ambulance
OL,5,Carrived
OL,7,F"I was holding her hand and talking to
OL,8,Fher and saying we'll get over this,
OL,9,Fit's alright, but in the blink of an
OL,10,Feyelid your whole world changes."
OL,12,FJennifer Baylis, an eyewitness said:
OL,13,F"She was incredibly stoic, she held it
OL,14,Ftogether so so well, you could she was
OL,15,Fin a phenomenal amount of pain but
OL,16,Fit's when she said to me I'm going to
OL,17,Fdie here tonight, that was
OL,18,Fheartbreaking to hear that and her
OL,19,Fhusband was saying they don't care
OL,20,Fabout us."
